WEBVTT

00:05.639 --> 00:07.772
               ¶ ¶              

00:08.976 --> 00:10.075
      This week on "Vice":      

00:10.176 --> 00:12.777
  The heated debate             
  surrounding the right to die. 

00:13.947 --> 00:15.947
     Assisting in the taking    
     of a human life            

00:16.049 --> 00:18.617
      is against everything     
      physicians stand for.     

00:18.719 --> 00:22.787
  When they are sitting         
  in this chair, then they can  
  make their own decision.      

00:22.889 --> 00:27.125
 We're about an hour            
 and 15 minutes from            
 when she's gonna end her life. 

00:28.294 --> 00:30.695
      (theme music playing)     

00:34.801 --> 00:35.867
            (gunshot)           

00:40.240 --> 00:42.941
        (crowd chanting)        

00:49.683 --> 00:51.783
               ¶ ¶              

00:54.587 --> 00:56.855
            So, how long        
            have you lived here?

00:56.957 --> 00:58.723
         In this house,         
         50 years.              

00:58.825 --> 01:02.360
        In my big house,        
        uh, 35.                 

01:02.462 --> 01:03.327
                      Okay.     

01:03.429 --> 01:04.663
      In the same village.      

01:04.765 --> 01:06.297
                    So, what was
                    here before?

01:06.399 --> 01:07.732
        Here was a table.       

01:07.834 --> 01:08.633
                      Yeah.     

01:08.735 --> 01:11.670
But tomorrow I lay here         
in my coffin.                   

01:11.772 --> 01:13.705
              Yeah, tomorrow    
              this is the space?
           Yeah.                

01:13.807 --> 01:14.673
              Yeah.             
                       Okay.    

01:14.775 --> 01:17.142
          So the table          
          must go away.         

01:18.211 --> 01:19.443
       You want a coffee?       

01:19.546 --> 01:20.845
               Yeah, I would    
               love some coffee.

01:20.947 --> 01:21.946
              Okay.             
                      Thank you.

01:22.049 --> 01:23.114
          Milk, sugar?          

01:23.216 --> 01:25.216
                    Uh, milk.   
                    Little milk.

01:25.318 --> 01:27.118
Little milk. Okay.              
                           Yeah.

01:28.755 --> 01:30.822
         Are you nervous at all?

01:30.924 --> 01:31.823
No.                             

01:31.925 --> 01:34.192
                             No?
       No.                      

01:34.294 --> 01:36.294
               No.              

01:36.396 --> 01:39.497
       It's all the people      
       who come around          

01:39.599 --> 01:42.200
     and have tears and cry,    

01:42.302 --> 01:45.103
   and that's difficult,        
   to say goodbye to everyone.  
                           Yeah.

01:46.106 --> 01:47.839
And that's what I wear.         

01:47.941 --> 01:50.842
It's special because            
I made it myself.               

01:50.944 --> 01:52.177
                Yeah, beautiful.

01:52.278 --> 01:55.947
It's on my card                 
to send around... I died.       

01:56.049 --> 01:57.882
Do you want                     
to see the photo?               

01:57.984 --> 01:59.684
Where I wear it?                
                     Yeah, sure.

01:59.786 --> 02:01.786
           So, we have          
           to go here.          

02:05.658 --> 02:09.360
      Feel so strong here,      
      so, yeah.                 

02:11.064 --> 02:13.531
         So glad, so...         

02:13.633 --> 02:16.667
       This come over           
       my case, my coffin.      

02:16.770 --> 02:20.504
 So, first, you are--           
 how do you call it in English? 

02:20.607 --> 02:22.240
A caterpillar?                  
                         Yeah.  

02:22.342 --> 02:24.508
          And then it's the road
          you have to go.       

02:24.611 --> 02:27.278
               And this are     
               the nice flowers,

02:27.380 --> 02:29.948
                   but there are
                  always stones.

02:30.050 --> 02:31.850
                The ugly stones.

02:31.952 --> 02:33.752
         So, it's about my life.

02:33.854 --> 02:36.221
When does someone               
become the butterfly?           

02:36.322 --> 02:37.488
                   When you die.

02:37.590 --> 02:38.757
When you die?                   
                   Yeah.        

02:38.859 --> 02:42.160
  I worked in a hospice,        
  so I've seen many dead people.

02:42.262 --> 02:44.963
           You can always see   
           that the soul go out.

02:45.065 --> 02:47.132
                 They are happy.

02:47.234 --> 02:49.367
                   Really happy.

02:51.238 --> 02:54.338
        Nothing matter anymore. 

